{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 11:10:40.636618", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report — Clos EBGP Lab\nPrepared observations date: (current capture)\n\n1) Executive summary\n- Overall fabric (super-spine, spines, most leaves and hosts) appears healthy and BGP-converged: most hosts can reach each other and routers (spine/super-spine/leaf_0_1) have full BGP tables for the 10.x/24 prefixes.\n- One clear anomaly: traffic from host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) is unable to reach other subnets. The problem localizes to leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1) — that leaf is not presenting/learning routes via BGP, and is returning ICMP Destination Unreachable for remote destinations.\n- Probable root cause: BGP adjacency problem on leaf_router_0_0 (either FRR/bgp daemon down or a BGP configuration issue — notably its local AS differs from the other leaf in the pod), causing the leaf to lack prefix information and to drop/blackhole non-local traffic.\n\n2) What is working (positive findings)\n- Bulk reachability tests across the lab (other pc_x_y hosts) mostly succeeded (0% loss in many pairwise tests).\n- Spine and super-spine routers show large, complete BGP tables and many learned paths for all 10.x/24 prefixes (evidence: show ip route and BGP tables on spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0 — they list the 31 10.x/24 routes and many paths).\n- leaf_router_0_1 and its attached host (pc_0_1) are functioning normally: leaf_router_0_1 has full BGP routes in its RIB and its 10.0.1.0/24 is properly connected and reachable by others.\n\n3) Detected anomalies and symptoms\n- PC-level symptoms:\n  - ping from pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) to remote host 10.2.3.2 (pc_2_3) failed with:\n    \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Net Unreachable\" (and 100% loss)\n  - ping from pc_0_0 to its neighbor pc_0_1 timed out (command timed out in test).\n  - In contrast, many other PCs (pc_0_1, others across pods) successfully ping pc_2_3 and pc_0_1 with low RTTs.\n- Router-level anomalies (leaf_router_0_0):\n  - leaf_router_0_0’s routing table (ip route) shows only directly connected networks (10.0.0.0/24 on eth8 and a set of local 172.16.*/31 interfaces), and there are no learned 10.x/24 prefixes in its routing table — i.e., it does not have BGP-learned routes to other tenant subnets.\n  - leaf_router_0_0’s BGP view contains only its local prefix (10.0.0.0/24) and shows local AS = 65800 (BGP table version = 1, local router ID 172.16.1.1). There are no learned prefixes from neighbors in that BGP instance.\n  - Neighbor leaf (leaf_router_0_1) shows proper BGP full view and its routing table contains numerous 10.x/24 entries (it is BGP-converged).\n  - Spines and super-spine have full BGP tables containing the leaf prefixes (indicating the rest of the fabric is exchanging routes).\n- ICMP evidence that the leaf (10.0.0.1) is responding that the destination is unreachable — which is consistent with that router not having a route for remote subnets.\n\n4) Localization — faulty device(s) / links\n- Primary faulty device: leaf_router_0_0 (the leaf that serves pc_0_0 / 10.0.0.0/24).\n- Suspect adjacency: BGP adjacency(s) between leaf_router_0_0 and its upstream spine(s) (example: link to spine_router_0_0 at 172.16.1.2) — sessions appear DOWN or not exchanging routes.\n- Impacted endpoints: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) and any hosts behind leaf_router_0_0; they cannot reach remote 10.x/24 subnets and are confined to local subnet only.\n\n5) Evidence excerpts (captured outputs)\n- pc_0_0 local config:\n  - eth0: inet 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1\n- Ping result from pc_0_0:\n  - To 10.2.3.2: \"From 10.0.0.1 icmp_seq=1 Destination Net Unreachable\" and 100% loss.\n  - To 10.0.1.2: ping attempt timed out.\n- leaf_router_0_0 interface and route info:\n  - eth8: inet 10.0.0.1/24 (connected)\n  - ip route shows 10.0.0.0/24 dev eth8 and many local 172.16.*/31 links, but no 10.x/24 learned routes present in the routing table.\n- leaf_router_0_0 BGP table:\n  - \"BGP table version is 1, local router ID is 172.16.1.1, local AS 65800\"\n  - Only entry: \"*> 10.0.0.0/24  0.0.0.0  32768 i\" (i.e., local/connected only; no external peers contributing routes)\n- leaf_router_0_1 (contrasting healthy leaf):\n  - BGP table shows \"*> 10.0.1.0/24 0.0.0.0 32768 i\" and many other 10.x/24 prefixes are present in its RIB (learned via BGP), and ip route shows those prefixes via BGP nexthops.\n- Spine and super-spine BGP outputs:\n  - Full set of 10.x/24 networks are present across spine and super-spine BGP tables — indicating inter-spine/super-spine routing is healthy.\n\n6) Probable root cause(s)\n- BGP adjacency failure on leaf_router_0_0. Two likely specific causes (based on captured state):\n  - BGP daemon/session is not established (FRR may be down on leaf_router_0_0 or neighbors not forming adjacency) — evidenced by the leaf's BGP table containing only the local prefix and no peers/learned prefixes.\n  - Configuration mismatch on leaf_router_0_0 BGP (notably, the leaf shows local AS = 65800 while other leaves in the pod use AS 65201 in the captured outputs). If the spine expects the leaf to use a specific remote-as, a misconfigured AS number will prevent adjacency formation. The AS discrepancy is a strong candidate for a configuration error preventing BGP peering.\n- Less likely causes (but possible): control-plane resource issues on leaf_router_0_0 (e.g., FRR process crashed, firewall blocking BGP TCP/179) — these would also show the same symptom (no BGP session / no routes). The data available most strongly supports a configuration/adjacency problem.\n\n7) Impact assessment\n- Host pc_0_0 and any endpoints behind leaf_router_0_0 cannot access remote subnets (all 10.x/24 outside their own /24).\n- Fabric-wide routing remains intact for other pods/leaves — the outage is localized to the single leaf and its connected host(s).\n- No evidence of wider instability (spines and super-spine BGP are healthy, other leaves are advertising and receiving prefixes).\n\n8) Recommended next investigation steps (for operator only — not mitigation)\n(These are investigative actions you may run next to confirm root cause; report does not include corrective actions.)\n- On leaf_router_0_0:\n  - Check FRR/BGP daemon status and logs (e.g., systemctl status frr and FRR logs) to confirm process health and peer session attempts.\n  - Show BGP neighbor summary/peers (vtysh show ip bgp summary) to confirm neighbor states and any error messages (AS mismatch, authentication issues, TCP reset, etc.).\n  - Check BGP neighbor configuration to confirm neighbor IP and remote-as values (compare remote-as against spine_router_0_0 configuration).\n  - Verify TCP connectivity to spine on TCP/179 from leaf_router_0_0 (e.g., telnet 172.16.1.2 179 or netstat to see established/timers).\n- On spine_router_0_0:\n  - Check BGP neighbor status for the session corresponding to 172.16.1.1 (leaf_router_0_0) to see if session attempted, and the exact reason for not establishing (show ip bgp neighbors).\n  - Check logs for any BGP errors with the leaf's IP (authentication/AS mismatch messages).\n- Compare BGP configuration (AS numbers, neighbor statements) between leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 to detect configuration drift.\n\n9) Conclusion\n- Network largely healthy except for a localized BGP adjacency failure at leaf_router_0_0. The observable symptoms (PC unreachable beyond local subnet, router returning Destination Net Unreachable, BGP table on leaf has only local prefix) strongly indicate that leaf_router_0_0 is not participating in EBGP with upstream spines. The captured config/state shows leaf_router_0_0 has a different local AS (65800) from the other leaf (65201), which likely explains the adjacency failure; alternatively, the FRR process may be down. The issue is localized and does not currently affect other pods/leaves.\n\nIf you want, I can now run the specific checks suggested above (BGP neighbor summary, FRR service status, or show ip bgp neighbors on the leaf and spine) to confirm which exact root cause (AS mismatch vs daemon down vs TCP/179 blockage) is the true cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 77961, "output_tokens": 4341, "total_tokens": 82302, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8832}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2176}}}
